        "text": "*[Bug 19022] New: Please add a check.names= argument to rbind.data.frame().*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19022>\n\n            Bug ID: 19022\n           Summary: Please add a check.names= argument to\n                    rbind.data.frame().\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: All\n                OS: All\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: enhancement\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Wishlist\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:p.krivitsky@unsw.edu.au|p.krivitsky@unsw.edu.au>\n\nBriefly, there does not appear to be a way to tell `rbind.data.frame()` that we\ndo not wish to rewrite the new column names to be syntactically valid variable\nnames.\n\nA MWE follows:\n```\n# Column name with a special character:\nl1 &lt;- list(`a\/b` = 1, c = 2)\nl2 &lt;- list(`a\/b` = 3, c = 4)\n\n# Column name converted:\nrbind.data.frame(l1, l2)\n#&gt;   a.b c\n#&gt; 1   1 2\n#&gt; 2   3 4\n\n# check.names has no effect:\nrbind.data.frame(l1, l2, check.names = FALSE)\n#&gt;   a.b c\n#&gt; 1   1 2\n#&gt; 2   3 4\n#&gt; 3   0 0\n\n# Converting to data frames first does:\nrbind(\n  do.call(data.frame, c(l1, check.names = FALSE)),\n  do.call(data.frame, c(l2, check.names = FALSE))\n)\n#&gt;   a\/b c\n#&gt; 1   1 2\n#&gt; 2   3 4\n```",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
